
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-jholland-idr-mcast-source-nexthop-over-amt-00.txt'>
    <title>"MBGP Extensions For Multicast Source Reachability Via AMT", Jake Holland</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-jholland-idr-mcast-source-nexthop-over-amt-00.txt</link>
    <description>This document describes a BGP-based method to communicate source IP reverse-path reachability for sources of multicast IP traffic which is available via AMT (RFC 7450).  This document defines a new SAFI (Subsequent Address Family Identifier) Parameter type for MBGP which declares the next hop for RPF (Reverse Path Forwarding) of a source IP to be the AMT tunnel discovered via an explicitly provided anycast IP address for AMT Relay Discovery.</description>
    <dc:date>2017-12-07T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
